        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 1:46AM MDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 146 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Glencross, or 11 miles east of Timber Lake, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Horse, Indian Memorial Rec Area, Little Moreau Rec Area,
Promise, Trail City, Grand River Casino, Glencross, and Blackfoot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
